K- Means Clustering¶

The k-means clustering method is an unsupervised machine learning technique used to identify clusters of data objects in a dataset.

There are many different types of clustering methods, but k-means is one of the oldest and most approachable.

Task to do¶

We load a drilling dataset from Hibernia 1638 Well and apply K- Means Clustering method to group similar data together.

In [9]:
# This function will generate a plot to identify optimum number of cluster

def optimise_k_means(data, max_k):
    means = []
    inertias = []
    
    for k in range(1,max_k):
        kmeans= KMeans(n_clusters =k)
        kmeans.fit(data)
        means.append(k)
        inertias.append(kmeans.inertia_)
        
    fig = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.plot(means, inertias, 'o-')
    plt.xlabel("Number of Clustersd")
    plt.ylabel("Inertia")
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()

Cluster visualization¶

ROBB vs. TNPH¶

In [15]:
# We will see distribution between ROBB and TNPH

fig,axs = plt.subplots(nrows =2, ncols =3, figsize = (15,10))

for i, ax in enumerate(fig.axes, start =1):
    ax.scatter(x=df['ROBB'], y= df['TNPH'], c= df[f'KMeans_{i}'], s=10)
    ax.set_ylabel('ROBB')
    ax.set_xlabel('TNPH')
    
    ax.set_title(f'N Clusters: {i}')
    fig.tight_layout()
